Author:
Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  The plan of what, we believe, was called at the Nelson diggings "blind dipping" has, we learn, been successfully practised at the Dunstan.  this is done by the miner standing in the water and taking up shovelfuls of stuff from the bottom.
